
1. How to build?
	step1: 
		Make sure you have installed kernel-default-source,kernel-default-devel
	step2: 
		Skip, if you have built your kernel before.
		Enter your kernel source "make oldconfig;make prepare;make modules_prepare;make"
	step3:
		make
2. How to use?
	step1:
		./netmonitor.sh start
	step2:
		./monitor_control -a -t -p 80 #add monitor tcp port 80
		...
		...


		./monitor_control -l #list all monitored port
	step3:
		./monitor_read #read all monitor date
	
3. What shoud I do?
	Write your reader function follow monitor_read.

